      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor just mentioned something about an escrow account for the closing and i'm kinda confused. what exactly is escrow and why do i need it for the house purchase?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of buying a house, is basically a temporary holding place for money and documents, like a secure, neutral third party holding things until all the conditions of the sale are met. Think of it like a very organized, very cautious middleman, which is a good thing because you don't want to hand over your entire payment to a seller who might suddenly decide to run off with it, right? It keeps everything orderly, ensuring that when the deal closes, both you and the seller get exactly what you agreed upon. This process is crucial because it protects both parties involved in the transaction.",
